Well, you could extend your argument to state that one of the most important things in Van Gogh&#x27;s life was to sever his own ear and hand it to a prostitute. Therefore, those who wish to become good painters ought to sever their ear. The fallacy in your argument is simply:
&quot;person x has done y, which led them to achievement z. therefore, if you do y, you will also achieve z, because person x had done so.&quot;
I don&#x27;t think this is a good way of refuting the parent comment, as disingenuous as it is.
